                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>SUBJECT</head>
                            <item>Correction in the Minority and Women Statistics for the 1979
                                Promotions</item>
                        </list>
                        <list type="references">
                            <head>REF</head>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_BHG_1">Barnes</persName>-<persName corresp="#p_RBH_1">Read</persName> memorandum on the same
                                subject of September 27<note n="2" xml:id="d229fn2">Not
                                    found.</note>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                        <p>Several errors in our statistics on women <gloss target="#t_FSO_1">FSO</gloss> promotions have been brought to our attention by <gloss target="#t_MEEO_1">M/EEO</gloss>. The corrected figures are
                            attached. They are essentially the same as those originally submitted
                            except at class 2, where the only woman promoted had been overlooked.
                            The correct figures, therefore, give a slightly more favorable picture
                            of women <gloss target="#t_FSO_1">FSO</gloss> promotions this year.</p>
